Hello
I am 30 years old.
I started doing coke at 20 years old.
I never took it every day, it wasn't super addictive.
I used to drink 1 or 2 times a month at most, but for about 6 months or even a year now, I can control myself when I drink alcohol.
Even though I used to promise myself not to go get some shnouf, after 2 or 3 drinks I start to get hot and think, "Well, we only have one life, it's parti-iiii" and it's impossible to control myself, I want to take more.
So here, I know the problem is alcohol at its core, but it's crazy, impossible to stop among family and friends for the apero, etc.
Has anyone this problem?
Thank you
Stop drinking and the problem will be solved.
Sometimes one has to be violent with oneself to stop ...
Have you at least talked to your family doctor about it?
seeing an addict might do you some good, especially for "evaluating" your consumption
