the day is going well
Hello,
I am a politox with a big problem of alcoholism,
I have been sober from alcohol for a few years, but I cannot tell myself that I will never drink another drop of alcohol, even though I want to, perhaps not enough willpower.
I sometimes have to restart on occasion because it's stronger than me, and as soon as I start, it's impossible for me to stop.
After I sleep very badly and I am sick the next day, and especially I hate myself,
I am ashamed of who I become when I drink and I suffer from it.
I can't drink normally.
I drink all my dry glasses.
Why do I have this connection with alcohol when so many people can drink normally?
I haven't drunk anything for 10 days.
This weekend I am invited to a birthday party and I am extremely scared,
If you understand me, have gone through the same thing or have passed the threshold, I will take anything that can help me.
Thank you for reading me and I look forward to your responses.
