Good morning to you Cllaude271. To start, I do not take LSD.
It happens that I take some speed (methamphetamine) or get high on pills, but not LSD, ketamine, or anything else.
I think you should simply see another doctor or a toxicologist (I don't know if that's the exact term).
If after 5 months you are still experiencing this kind of "side effect," it's really bad.
So without wanting to panic you, you should see a toxicologist who, I think, will prescribe an emergency treatment or medication.
Otherwise there are green numbers or specialized forums. Good continuation. Peace
Hello Claude271,
Having gone through the state you describe many times (due to a mix of chatterboxes, micropoints, taz, keta, in short, everything that passed through there),
If I can give you a tip, it's simply to tell yourself that all of this is just psychological.
In short, the more you stress about these states, the worse they will get.
In such cases, a very simple thing to do is to take deep breaths, breathe gently, and settle in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes, sometimes you might feel like they are closing in on you).
After several months following a use, especially when you mix them, you can experience effects, particularly after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude532 used to say, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of those voices cluttering your head.
Stay strong and stay positive.
Thank you both for your responses
I will try to be patient.
